Another noteworthy trend in the market is the integration of artificial intelligence and machine learning capabilities in application development and modernization processes. By leveraging AI-driven tools, organizations can automate repetitive tasks, optimize code quality, and gain valuable insights from data to enhance the overall application performance and user experience. This trend is particularly significant for large enterprises dealing with complex legacy systems that require intelligent modernization strategies to meet the evolving business demands. Additionally, the increasing emphasis on cybersecurity in application development is driving the demand for secure coding practices, vulnerability assessments, and continuous security monitoring to protect sensitive data and mitigate potential cyber threats.

